  "behavior": "I avoid reaching out or responding to the estranged person. I reinforce my boundaries by not engaging, even if I feel lonely or conflicted.",
  "rationale": "\"There may be a tendency to anticipate negative outcomes in relationships, leading to hyper-vigilance or mistrust.\" \"The decision to avoid reconnecting with the estranged person suggests a cognitive shift towards self-preservation and boundary-setting.\" \"The patient might also engage in rumination about past conflicts or perceived failures in relationships, which could perpetuate feelings of guilt or self-doubt.\" \"Behaviorally, the patient may exhibit avoidance of situations or individuals that are perceived as threatening or harmful, as evidenced by the decision not to reconnect with the estranged person.\""
